<template><div><h1 id="what-is-lemu" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#what-is-lemu" aria-hidden="true">#</a> What is LEMU?</h1>
<p>Lemu is a desktop application to configure and run your <a href="https://github.com/garris/BackstopJS" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BackstopJS<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>. It aims to provide a simple and guided experience towards building your test scenario for people more accustomed to GUI than configuration files and command line interface.</p>
<p>You can download Lemu on the official GitHub repository in the <a href="https://github.com/Vince-F/lemu/releases" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">releases section<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>. Builds are available for Windows, Linux and MacOS.</p>
<p>To know how to start using Lemu jump into the <a href="/guide/getting-started">Getting sarted</a> section.</p>
